comments: Adams (OKC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Ingram's (NOP) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact during the screen. The contact that occurs as Adams turns is deemed marginal.
Ingram (NOP) and Gallinari (OKC) briefly engage in marginal contact as both players move around the screen.

Adams (OKC) delivers some contact to Ingram (NOP) during the pick but the contact is marginal. Adams' left arm is away from his body but he does not extend it. Ingram's reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Ingram (NOP) makes contact to Adams' (OKC) body that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Hayes (NOP) slightly extends his arm into Ferguson (OKC) during the pick but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend.
Holiday (NOP) slightly leans forward into Ferguson (OKC) and initiates some contact prior to the jump shot attempt. The marginal contact does not affect Ferguson's ability to defend.
Adams (OKC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Holiday's (NOP) path and is firming up over his right leg when the contact occurs during the pick.
Ingram (NOP) makes marginal contact to Adams' (OKC) arm that does not affect his ability to gather the ball.
Hart (NOP) makes hand on ball contact with Adams (OKC) during the upward shooting motion on his shot attempt near the rim.
Hayes (NOP) makes contact to Adams' (OKC) head during his shot attempt near the rim.
Hayes (NOP) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and is firming up when the contact occurs during the pick.
As a progressing player, Ingram (NOP) gathers the pass on his right foot and then steps with his left foot, making that his pivot foot.
Holiday (NOP) reaches in and makes contact with the ball during Paul's (OKC) dribble.
Ingram (NOP) makes contact to Adams' (OKC) body that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Hart (NOP) arrive at the ball simultaneously. Both players make clean contact with the ball during the rebound.
Paul (OKC) briefly grasps Redick's (NOP) arm off ball but the contact is marginal and does not affect Redick's ability to move freely.
After absorbing the contact from the screen, Gallinari (OKC) places a hand on Holiday's (NOP) back but he immediately slides it off. The contact is deemed marginal.
Hayes (NOP) slightly extends his arms into Ferguson (OKC) during the pick but the marginal contact does not affect Ferguson's ability to defend.
Redick (NOP) and Paul (OKC) mutually engage and disengage off ball.
Ingram (NOP) places a hand on Paul's (OKC) body but Paul jumps away from the marginal contact during his shot attempt.
Ferguson (OKC) initiates some body contact to Holiday (NOP) during the drive but he is able to move through the marginal contact and continue his drive.
Holiday (NOP) slightly extends his arm and initiates some contact to Ferguson (OKC) at the end of the drive but his momentum carries him away from the marginal contact.
Hart (NOP) commits the personal take foul on Gallinari (OKC).
